  "text": "As stated before, studies on the inflammatory reaction in GITR -/-mice show decreased inflammation compared to wild type mice. A study on these mice showed that the GITR/GITRL system favors resistance to CIA, proven by less IFNγ, IL-6, TNFα, macrophage inflammatory protein-1 (MIP-1), and MIP-2 secretion [CITATION_1] . In GITR -/-mice, resistance to TNBS-induced colitis correlated with less IL-12, TNF-α and IL-6 produced by lamina propria mononuclear cells. Moreover, CD4",
